    HEADLINE
    ────────
    Morris of Rutherglen Finishes Single Malt in Its Own Tokay Casks

    ANGLE
    ─────
    Morris Whisky in Rutherglen has a structural advantage few Australian distillers can match: a working fortified-wine operation dating to 1859 that supplies its own cooperage. Head distiller Darren Peck finishes the house single malt in Morris's own Rutherglen fortified casks — tokay among them — producing a flavour signature that bought-in barrels cannot replicate. With a refurbished cellar door pouring whisky alongside the fortifieds and a Tokay Barrel expression already on Halliday's radar, this is a story about provenance you can taste in the glass.

